    "For learning-based translators, we reproduce them using their published source code and load them with the optimal weights for each translation dataset.Following that, we fix their 𝑏𝑒𝑎𝑚_𝑠𝑖𝑧𝑒s=10 and fetch their first outputs for re-evaluation during inference on the cleaned dataset.",
    "Towards UniTrans, the settings of its backbone LLMs are kept as default.",
    "In the Translation Augmentation Phase, considering the trade-off between performance and efficiency, we randomly select 3 generated test cases to construct Translation Augmentation Prompts.",
    "Besides, in the Translation Repair Phase, we leverage LLMs to repair error programs for 1 round as the default setting, considering the efficiency issue.",
    "Research Questions and Evaluation MethodologyHere, we introduce six research questions of this work and propose our evaluation methodology.RQ1: What is the performance of recent LLMs against state-of-the-art learning-based transpilers in code translation?"
